Demystifying the Journey: What Happens When You Type "https://www.google.com" in Your Browser?

Introduction:
Opening remarks about the complexity behind the scenes when a simple action like typing a URL and pressing Enter initiates a series of intricate processes.

DNS Request:
Explanation of how the Domain Name System (DNS) converts the human-readable URL "www.google.com" into an IP address that the computer can understand.
Elaboration on the steps involved in DNS resolution and how caching plays a role in optimizing this process.

TCP/IP:
Discussion on the Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) and Internet Protocol (IP) and their roles in establishing a connection between the client (browser) and the server (Google's web servers).
Explanation of the handshake process and the packet delivery mechanism used in TCP/IP.

Firewall:
Brief overview of firewalls and their purpose in filtering network traffic, ensuring security by monitoring and controlling incoming and outgoing network traffic based on predetermined security rules.

HTTPS/SSL:
Insight into the significance of HTTPS (Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure) and SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) in securing the communication between the client and the server.
Description of how SSL/TLS handshake occurs, enabling encryption and ensuring data integrity.

Load-Balancer:
Explanation of load balancers and their role in distributing incoming network traffic across multiple servers to enhance reliability, optimize resource utilization, and prevent overloading of any single server.

Web Server:
Details about the web server's role in handling client requests, serving web pages, and interacting with the browser to fulfill the requested content.

Application Server:
Discussion on application servers and their responsibility for executing the logic behind dynamic content generation, handling server-side scripting, database queries, etc.

Database:
Insight into the database server's role in storing and retrieving data requested by the application server, completing the flow of information necessary to render the requested web page.

Conclusion:
Recap of the sequential steps involved in the journey from typing a URL to rendering a webpage, emphasizing the collaboration of various components in the web stack.
